snippet.textDisplay:
Quick comment on the bosses from a guy who somehow has more hours then you in this game. I don't think Sekiro has any "bad" bosses, just not bosses that stand up to the quality of the other bosses. Folding Screen Monkeys, in my opinion, is not a bad boss. For a first run and for thematic and lore relevance, it's actually quite good. It's just that replaying the game makes it a roadblock. Thankfully, the boss rush mode pretty much solves that issue for me. 

Hell, even the bosses that aren't high on the tier lists are decent enough. Headless Ape Duo doesn't compare to the rest of the bosses, because the rest are so good. If that fight was in a Ubisoft game, people would be raving about how well thought out and creative it is. It's a fun rematch and finishing it off with the Mortal Blade never gets old.

Other than that there aren't any other bosses that I could call bad. Divine Dragon is maybe From's best gimmick/setpiece fight ever, and from Gyoubu through to the Sword Saint himself, the bar remains high. 

Apart from the needless hate on Dark Souls which are all landmark games and incredible in there own rights, good video!
